HIV/AIDS: China ta ba da rahoton karuwar sabbin masu cutar da kashi 14 cikin dari
China ta ce adadin mutanen da ke fama da cutar kanjamau da kanjamau ya karu da kashi 14 cikin dari.
A cewar jami'an lafiya, mutane sama da 820,000 ne suka kamu da cutar a kasar.
A cikin kwata na biyu na 2018 kadai, an samu sabbin mutane kusan 40,000.
Yawancin sabbin cututtukan suna yaduwa ta hanyar jima'i, wanda ke nuna canji daga abin da ya gabata.
A wasu sassan kasar Sin, cutar HIV ta yadu cikin sauri ta hanyar amfani da jini daga mutane masu cutar, wanda aka yi amfani da shi don maye gurbin jini.
Amma, a wani taron da aka yi a lardin Yunnan, jami'an kiwon lafiya na kasar Sin sun ce an kusan kawar da cutar HIV.
Duk da haka, adadin mutanen da ke fama da cutar kanjamau da kanjamau a ƙasar Sin yana ƙaruwa da miliyan ɗaya a kowace shekara.
Yaduwar cutar HIV ta hanyar jima'i tsakanin al'ummomin LGBT a China babbar matsala ce.
Kasar Sin ta haramta luwadi a shekarar 1997, duk da haka nuna bambanci ga mutanen LGBT ya ci gaba da kasancewa a cikin mummunan yanayi.
Bincike ya nuna cewa, saboda tsayayyun dabi'u a kasar, kashi 70-90 cikin dari na maza da ke yin jima'i da maza za su auri matan.
Sau da yawa, cututtuka suna yaduwa ne saboda maza ba sa samun kariya ta jima'i lokacin da suke yin jima'i da juna.
A kokarin magance matsalar, tun daga 2003, gwamnatin kasar Sin ta yi alkawarin samar da maganin HIV ga kowa.
